Enum MessageType

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<MessageType>
      • it.polimi.ingsw.network.common.message.MessageType

    public enum MessageType
extends java.lang.Enum<MessageType>

    This enumeration contains all the possible type of NetworkMessage that can be sent and/or received from all possible entities.

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • PING_MESSAGE

        public static final MessageType PING_MESSAGE
        A PING_MESSAGE represents a type of message sent from the server application to all the clients connected. It is used to keep track of a client disconnections through its continuous sent (heart-beat protocol). If a PING_MESSAGE fails to be delivered, a connection issue is plausible and further actions may be taken to respond to this unwanted situation.

      • REGISTER_REQUEST

        public static final MessageType REGISTER_REQUEST
        A REGISTER_REQUEST represents a type of message sent from all the clients to server. It is used to ask the server to perform a registration routine, at the end of which the client is stably connected and can take exclusive actions that wouldn't have been possible without the authentication step.

      • REGISTER_SUCCESS

        public static final MessageType REGISTER_SUCCESS
        A REGISTER_SUCCESS represents a type of message sent from the server to all the clients connected. It is used to notify a client that the authentication routine has been successful and he is now stably registered onto the server.

      • CLIENT_ALREADY_REGISTERED_ERROR

        public static final MessageType CLIENT_ALREADY_REGISTERED_ERROR
        A CLIENT_ALREADY_REGISTERED_ERROR represents a type of message sent from the server to all the clients connected. It is used to notify a client that another client has been previously registered with the same credentials and therefore his request has been rejected.

      • UNREGISTER_REQUEST

        public static final MessageType UNREGISTER_REQUEST
        A UNREGISTER_REQUEST represents a type of message sent from all the clients to server. It is used to ask the server to perform an unregistering routine, at the end of which the client is safely disconnected. After this step no further information about the client has been kept on the server.

      • UNREGISTER_SUCCESS

        public static final MessageType UNREGISTER_SUCCESS
        An UNREGISTER_SUCCESS represents a type of message sent from the server to all the clients connected. It is used to notify a client that the unregistering routine has been successful and he is no longer connected to the sever; as a result there will be no client information left on the server.

      • CLIENT_NOT_REGISTERED_ERROR

        public static final MessageType CLIENT_NOT_REGISTERED_ERROR
        A CLIENT_NOT_REGISTERED_ERROR represents a type of message sent from the server to all the clients connected. It is used to notify a client that there are no clients previously connected to the server that matches the credentials of the caller and, for that reason, no unregistering routine has been executed.

      • LOBBY_LIST_UPDATE_REQUEST

        public static final MessageType LOBBY_LIST_UPDATE_REQUEST
        A LOBBY_LIST_UPDATE_REQUEST represents a type of message sent from the clients to server. It is used to ask the server for the list of all available Lobby.

      • LOBBY_LIST_UPDATE_RESPONSE

        public static final MessageType LOBBY_LIST_UPDATE_RESPONSE
        A LOBBY_LIST_UPDATE_RESPONSE represents a type of message sent from the server to all the clients connected. It is used to indicate that the current NetworkMessage contains the requested Lobby list update, usually asked via a LOBBY_LIST_UPDATE_REQUEST type of message.

      • LOBBY_CREATE_REQUEST

        public static final MessageType LOBBY_CREATE_REQUEST
        A LOBBY_CREATE_REQUEST represents a type of message sent from all the clients to server. It is used to ask the server to create a new Lobby with the information given in the trailer of the attached NetworkMessage.

      • LOBBY_CREATE_SUCCESS

        public static final MessageType LOBBY_CREATE_SUCCESS
        a LOBBY_CREATE_SUCCESS represents a type of message sent from the server to all the clients connected. It is used to notify a client that the creation of a new Lobby has been successful and now it's available for connecting clients.

      • LOBBY_ALREADY_EXISTS_ERROR

        public static final MessageType LOBBY_ALREADY_EXISTS_ERROR
        A LOBBY_ALREADY_EXISTS_ERROR represents a type of message sent from the server to all the clients connected. It is used to notify a client that another Lobby with the same identifier has already been created and, as a result, no new lobbies have been registered on the server.

      • LOBBY_NOT_FOUND_ERROR

        public static final MessageType LOBBY_NOT_FOUND_ERROR
        A LOBBY_NOT_FOUND_ERROR represents a type of message sent from the server to all the clients connected. It is used to notify a client that the requested Lobby was not found on the server and therefore no further actions have ben taken.

      • LOBBY_FULL_ERROR

        public static final MessageType LOBBY_FULL_ERROR
        A LOBBY_NOT_FOUND_ERROR represents a type of message sent from the server to all the clients connected. It is used to notify a client that the Lobby he is trying to connecting to has reached tme maximum amount of participants and therefore no join operation have been performed.

      • LOBBY_LOGIN_REQUEST

        public static final MessageType LOBBY_LOGIN_REQUEST
        A LOBBY_LOGIN_REQUEST represents a type of message sent from all the clients to server. It is used to ask the server to login to a specified Lobby whose information are specified in the trailer of the actual NetworkMessage.

      • LOBBY_LOGIN_SUCCESS

        public static final MessageType LOBBY_LOGIN_SUCCESS
        a LOBBY_LOGIN_SUCCESS represents a type of message sent from the server to all the clients connected. It is used to notify a client that the login request performed to join a Lobby has been successful.

      • PLAYER_ALREADY_ADDED_ERROR

        public static final MessageType PLAYER_ALREADY_ADDED_ERROR
        A PLAYER_ALREADY_ADDED_ERROR represents a type of message sent from the server to all the clients connected. It is used to notify a client that another Player with the same identifier has already joined the specified Lobby and as a result, no login routine has been performed.

      • PASSWORD_NOT_VALID_ERROR

        public static final MessageType PASSWORD_NOT_VALID_ERROR
        A PASSWORD_NOT_VALID_ERROR represents a type of message sent from the server to all the clients connected. It is used to notify a client that the given password for the chosen Lobby does not match and therefore the login procedure has failed.

      • GAME_ALREADY_STARTED_ERROR

        public static final MessageType GAME_ALREADY_STARTED_ERROR
        A GAME_ALREADY_STARTED_ERROR represents a type of message sent from the server to all the clients connected. It is used to notify a client that he no longer can access the selected Lobby because the corresponding Game has started and therefore, the login procedure has failed.

      • LOBBY_LOGOUT_REQUEST

        public static final MessageType LOBBY_LOGOUT_REQUEST
        A LOBBY_LOGOUT_REQUEST represents a type of message sent from all the clients to server. It is used to ask the server to log out a client from a specified Lobby whose information are specified in the trailer of the actual NetworkMessage.

      • LOBBY_LOGOUT_SUCCESS

        public static final MessageType LOBBY_LOGOUT_SUCCESS
        a LOBBY_LOGOUT_SUCCESS represents a type of message sent from the server to all the clients connected. It is used to notify a client that the logout request performed to exit a Lobby has been successful.

      • LOBBY_EMPTY_ERROR

        public static final MessageType LOBBY_EMPTY_ERROR
        A LOBBY_EMPTY_ERROR represents a type of message sent from the server to all the clients connected. It is used to notify a client that the Lobby he is trying to log out from empty and and therefore no logout operation have been performed.

      • PLAYER_NOT_FOUND_ERROR

        public static final MessageType PLAYER_NOT_FOUND_ERROR
        A PLAYER_NOT_FOUND_ERROR represents a type of message sent from the server to all the clients connected. It is used to notify a client that no Player that corresponds to the given identifier has been found in the Players list.

      • CLIENT_MESSAGE

        public static final MessageType CLIENT_MESSAGE
        A CLIENT_MESSAGE represents a type of message sent bidirectionally from both the clients and the server. It is used to send non network related content through the communication infrastructure. These type of messages are not handled directly from the communication layer, but they need to be processed from an appropriate interpreter at an higher level. These messages always include a content that can't be checked or parsed from the network level.

      • COUNTDOWN_UPDATE

        public static final MessageType COUNTDOWN_UPDATE
        A COUNTDOWN_UPDATE represents a type of message sent from the server to all the clients connected. It is used to notify a client every time a relevant timer-related update is triggered. This may occur, as an example, the if the countdown jumps from a value to another not adjacent as a result of some time logic manipulation.

      • COUNTDOWN_EXPIRED

        public static final MessageType COUNTDOWN_EXPIRED
        A COUNTDOWN_EXPIRED represents a type of message sent from the server to all the clients connected. It is used to notify a client about the timer expiration. A typical scenario of usage is when the local countdown (autonomous from the server) reaches zero while (because of delay) a COUNTDOWN_UPDATE is missing or late.In this situation the Game wont start until this last message is sent.

      • COUNTDOWN_STOPPED

        public static final MessageType COUNTDOWN_STOPPED
        A COUNTDOWN_STOPPED represents a type of message sent from the server to all the clients connected. It is used to notify a client that the countdown has been stopped or paused. This happens, as an example, if too many Players disconnects from the Lobby and therefore, there are not enough Players left to allow the Game to start.

      • OPPONENTS_LIST_UPDATE

        public static final MessageType OPPONENTS_LIST_UPDATE
        A OPPONENTS_LIST_UPDATE represents a type of message sent from the server to all the clients connected. It is used to notify a client with the collection of all the Players logged into his same Lobby.
